'''Nicolás Paz Martínez''' (born 8 September 2004) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Como}} club [[Como 1907|Como]]. Born in Spain, he plays for the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Club career==
===Youth career===
A youth product of CD San Juan and [[CD Tenerife|Tenerife]], Paz joined the Real Madrid's ''[[La Fábrica (Real Madrid)|La Fábrica]]'' in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/futbol/cantera/juvenil-c/nicolas-paz-martinez|title=Profile|accessdate=17 April 2022|publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref>

Initially starting his career as a central defender, Paz moved further up the pitch as he developed. After playing as a centre forward, he switched to the wing, where he played for the [[Real Madrid Juvenil|under-19 side]]. He is also comfortable operating as a central midfielder or playmaker.<ref name=as>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2022/03/07/soccer/1646654951_388869.html|title=Who is Nico Paz? From Real Madrid's youth academy to the Argentina senior side|first=Andy|last=Hall|date=7 March 2022|accessdate=17 April 2022|website=en.as.com|archive-date=4 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221104074109/https://en.as.com/en/2022/03/07/soccer/1646654951_388869.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elfutbolero.es/laliga/Quien-es-Nico-Paz-y-cuantos-millones-cuesta-la-gran-promesa-del-Real-Madrid-20220307-0005.html|title=¿Quién es Nico Paz y cuantos millones cuesta la gran promesa del Real Madrid?|trans-title=Who is Nico Paz and how many millions does the great promise of Real Madrid cost?|first=Tomás|last=Valle|date=7 March 2022|accessdate=17 April 2022|website=elfutbolero.es|language=Spanish|archive-date=4 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221104074105/https://www.elfutbolero.es/laliga/Quien-es-Nico-Paz-y-cuantos-millones-cuesta-la-gran-promesa-del-Real-Madrid-20220307-0005.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
Paz made his senior debut for [[Real Madrid Castilla]] in a 3–1 win over [[FC Andorra|Andorra]] in January 2022, coming on as an 82nd-minute substitute for [[Iván Morante]].<ref name=as/>

On 8 November 2023, Paz made his first-team and [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut for [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in a [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]] match against [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] as a substitute in the 77th minute to replace [[Federico Valverde]] at [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 November 2023 |title=Nico Paz makes his Real Madrid debut |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/11/08/nico-paz-makes-his-real-madrid-debut |access-date=9 November 2023 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |archive-date=9 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231109041301/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/11/08/nico-paz-makes-his-real-madrid-debut |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 November 2023 |title=Real Madrid-Braga: UEFA Champions League 2023/24 Group stage |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039144--real-madrid-vs-braga/ |access-date=9 November 2023 |publisher=UEFA |archive-date=8 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231108195107/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039144--real-madrid-vs-braga/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 11 November 2023, Paz made his [[La Liga]] debut in a 5–1 victory over [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], coming on as a substitute in the 82nd minute for [[Dani Carvajal]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-11 |title=Real Madrid vs Valencia CF |url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2023-2024-laliga-easports-real-madrid-valencia-cf-13 |access-date=2023-11-12 |publisher=La Liga |language=en |archive-date=2023-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719161036/https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2023-2024-laliga-easports-real-madrid-valencia-cf-13 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-11 |title=Real Madrid 5–1 Valencia: Player ratings as Los Blancos run riot |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/real-madrid-5-1-valencia-player-ratings-11-11-2023 |access-date=2023-11-12 |website=90min |language=en-GB |archive-date=2023-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231112045605/https://www.90min.com/posts/real-madrid-5-1-valencia-player-ratings-11-11-2023 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 29 November, he scored his first goal in the Champions League, securing a 4–2 win against [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2023/11/29/nico-paz-overwhelmed-after-scoring-first-real-madrid-goal-in-napoli-victory-this-is-a-dream |title=Nico Paz overwhelmed after scoring first Real Madrid goal in Napoli victory – "This is a dream" |publisher=Football España |date=29 November 2023 |access-date=30 November 2023 |archive-date=29 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231129223536/https://www.football-espana.net/2023/11/29/nico-paz-overwhelmed-after-scoring-first-real-madrid-goal-in-napoli-victory-this-is-a-dream |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Como===
On 25 August 2024, Paz signed for newly promoted [[Serie A]] club [[Como 1907|Como]] on a four-year deal for a reported €6 million fee.<ref>{{cite web |date=25 August 2024 |title=Como 1907 annuncia l'astro nascente del Real Madrid e nazionale giovanile argentino Nico Paz |url=https://comofootball.com/como-1907-annuncia-lastro-nascente-del-real-madrid-e-nazionale-giovanile-argentino-nico-paz/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240829120147/https://comofootball.com/como-1907-annuncia-lastro-nascente-del-real-madrid-e-nazionale-giovanile-argentino-nico-paz/ |archive-date=29 August 2024 |access-date=25 August 2024 |publisher=Como 1907 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-25 |title=Official Announcement: Nico Paz |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/club/announcements/comunicado-oficial-nico-paz-25-08-2024 |access-date=2024-08-25 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref> The following day, he made his debut for the club, coming on as a substitute in a 1–1 draw against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Serie A <nowiki>|</nowiki> Cagliari 1–1 Como: Match Report |url=https://www.footitalia.com/serie-a-cagliari-1-1-como/ |website=Football Italia |access-date=26 August 2024 |date=26 August 2024}}</ref> On 19 October, he scored his first goal for Como in a 1–1 draw against [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Serie A <nowiki>|</nowiki> Como 1–1 Parma: Paz replies to spectacular Bonny strike |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/serie-como-1-1-parma-145700251.html |website=Football Italia |publisher=Yahoo Sports |access-date=1 November 2024 |date=19 October 2024}}</ref>

After registering six goals and nine assists in his debut season in Italy, Paz was named Best Under-23 player at the [[2024–25 Serie A|2024–25]] [[Serie A Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/real-madrid-very-close-re-signing-breakout-star-2025-club-world-cup|title=Real Madrid ‘Very Close’ to Re-Signing Breakout Star for 2025 Club World Cup|date=27 May 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> He was also included in the 23-man squad for Serie A Team of the Season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ea.com/en-au/games/ea-sports-fc/fc-25/tots/serie-a|title=Serie A Enilive Team of the Season|access-date=13 January 2026|website=EA Sports}}</ref> 

In August 2025, [[Sky Sport Italia]] reported that Como had rejected an offer of €50m for Paz from English [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sport.sky.it/calciomercato/2025/08/24/nico-paz-tottenham-como-calciomercato-news|title=Nico Paz, il Tottenham alza l'offerta a 50 milioni ma il Como dice no: le news di mercato|date=24 August 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=Sky Sport Italia}}</ref>

Paz was assigned Como's #10 shirt ahead of the [[2025–26 Como 1907 season|2025–26 season]]. On 24 August, in the opening match of the [[2025–26 Serie A|Serie A season]], Paz provided an assist and scored a goal from a free-kick to give Como a 2–0 win against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/articles/soccer/nico-paz-shines-as-como-beats-lazio-20-in-serie-a.com|title=Official &#124; Nico Paz shines as Como beats Lazio 2-0 in Serie A|first=foxsports.com|last=Fox Sports|date=24 August 2025|website=Fox Sports}}</ref> He continued his strong start to the season by scoring in the next two home matches against [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/italia/nota/_/id/15680641/video-gol-nico-paz-como-vs-genoa-fecha-3-serie-a|title=Golazo de Nico Paz en el empate de Como ante Genoa, por la Serie A|language=Spanish|date=15 September 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=ESPN Deportes}}</ref> and [[US Cremonese|Cremonese]] respectively,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Como/27-09-2025/como-cremonese-1-1-gol-di-nico-paz-baschirotto.shtml?refresh_ce|title=Il solito Nico Paz non basta al Como. La Cremonese strappa un punto con Baschirotto|language=Italian|date=27 September 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=Gazzetta dello Sport}}</ref> as well as assisting both of the team's goals in a 2–1 win at [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/futbol/dos-asistencias-de-nico-paz-y-una-de-matias-soule-para-los-triunfos-de-como-y-roma-en-italia-nid21092025/|title=Dos asistencias de Nico Paz y una de Matías Soulé para los triunfos de Como y Roma en Italia|language=Spanish|date=21 September 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=La Nación}}</ref> This form saw him named Serie A's "Rising Star of the Month" for September 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://static.legaseriea.it/en/media/serie-a/nico-paz-rising-star-of-the-month-14d45ilggd40ho|title=Nico Paz “Rising Star Of The Month”|date=8 October 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=Lega Serie A}}</ref> On 19 October, Paz assisted [[Marc-Oliver Kempf]]'s opening goal and scored his team's second as Como defeated [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] for the first time since 1952.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20251019-paz-fires-high-flying-como-to-historic-win-over-juve|title=Paz fires high-flying Como to historic win over Juve|date=19 October 2025|access-date=13 January 2026|website=France 24}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in [[Santa Cruz de Tenerife]], Canary Islands, Paz was eligible to represent both Spain and Argentina at international level.<ref name=wf/> He was first called up to the senior [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]] in March 2022.<ref name=as/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ar.marca.com/claro/futbol/seleccion-argentina/2022/03/07/62255204e2704e05658b459b.html|title=¿Quiénes son Nico Paz y Alejandro Garnacho, los talentos españoles que sorprendieron a Scaloni?|trans-title=Who are Nico Paz and Alejandro Garnacho, the Spanish talents that surprised Scaloni?|first=Jorge|last=Caballero|date=7 March 2022|accessdate=17 April 2022|work=Marca|language=Spanish|archive-date=26 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220326131650/https://ar.marca.com/claro/futbol/seleccion-argentina/2022/03/07/62255204e2704e05658b459b.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Paz also was called up to the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina under-20 side]] for the [[2022 Maurice Revello Tournament]] in France.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/convocados-de-la-sub-20-para-el-torneo-maurice-revello|title=Convocados de la Sub 20 para el Torneo Maurice Revello|trans-title=Sub 20: all the information on the Maurice Revello Tournament|website=afa.com.ar|publisher=Argentine Football Association|date=20 May 2022|accessdate=30 May 2022|language=Spanish|archive-date=31 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531184506/https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/convocados-de-la-sub-20-para-el-torneo-maurice-revello|url-status=live}}</ref> He was later named in Argentina's preliminary 48-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Hancock |first1=Greg Lea Contributions from Tom |last2=published |first2=Alasdair Mackenzie |date=2022-11-02 |title=Argentina World Cup 2022 squad: Lionel Scaloni announces 48-man longlist |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/argentina-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar |access-date=2022-11-04 |website=fourfourtwo.com |language=en |archive-date=2022-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221218133642/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/argentina-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 15 October 2024, Paz made his senior debut for Argentina in a 6–0 win over [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] match, recording an assist for [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/sports/messi-shines-at-monumental-as-albiceleste-thrash-bolivia.phtml |title=Hat-trick hero Messi shines at Monumental as Argentina thrash Bolivia |publisher=Buenos Aires Times |date=15 October 2024 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Nico Paz is widely recognized as a modern "[[Midfielder|number 10]]" and known for his dribbling, playmaking and shooting abilities.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-04 |title=Nico Paz at Como: The Rise of Serie A Young Midfield Maestro - Breaking The Lines |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/nico-paz-at-como-the-rise-of-serie-a-young-midfield-maestro/ |access-date=2025-12-09 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Paz is the son of former Argentine international [[Pablo Paz]], who played at the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]] in France.<ref name=as/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/elbernabeu/real-madrid/cantera/20220307/nico-paz-promesa-real-madrid-scaloni-argentina/655434518_0.html|title=¿Quiénes son Nico Paz y Alejandro Garnacho, los talentos españoles que sorprendieron a Scaloni?|trans-title=Nico Paz, the promise of Real Madrid that falls in love with Scaloni: called up by Argentina at only 17 years old|first=Borja|last=Sánchez|date=7 March 2022|accessdate=17 April 2022|website=elespanol.com|language=Spanish|archive-date=17 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220417141556/https://www.elespanol.com/elbernabeu/real-madrid/cantera/20220307/nico-paz-promesa-real-madrid-scaloni-argentina/655434518_0.html|url-status=live}}</ref> His mother is Spanish.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deportestvc.com/futbol-internacional/nico-paz-padres-este-es-el-origen-del-padre-madre-y-hermanas-del-futbolista-del-real-madrid-2023-12-01|title=Nico Paz padres, este es el origen del padre, madre y hermanas del futbolista del Real Madrid|date=December 2023 }}</ref>

